The National Institute for Communicable Diseases (NICD) has reported 1 888 new COVID-19 cases that have been identified in South Africa, which brings the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases to 3 718 953. This increase represents a 6.4% positivity rate. The majority of new cases on Thursday are from Gauteng (39%), followed by KwaZulu-Natal (22%). The institute has also recorded one COVID-19 related death. “Today, the NDoH reports 12 deaths and of these, one occurred in the past 24 – 48 hours. This brings the total fatalities to 100 032 to date.” The majority of new cases today are from Gauteng (39%), followed by KwaZulu-Natal (22%). 23 838 911 tests have been conducted in both public and private sectors. Below are the latest coronavirus statistics:   Loading… (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document));